  <Method>
    <Step image="">Put  rice in a chinois or mesh colander and rinse under cold running water, drain.</Step>
    <Step image="Wild%20Rice%20Stuffing_ww3.jpg">Put rice and 1 tsp salt in a sauce pan with stock.  Set pot to boil, then reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 45-55 minutes, until rice kernels are open and tender, but not mushy.  Turn rice into colander and let set to cool. </Step>
    <Step image="Wild%20Rice%20Stuffing_ww2.jpg">Put butter In a sauté pan over medium heat to melt. Add onions and shallots, sauté until lightly browned.  </Step>
    <Step image="Wild%20Rice%20Stuffing_ww5.jpg">Remove from heat, stir herbs into the mixture, then add rice and toss, adding truffle oil, until well mixed.  Season with salt and pepper. </Step>
  </Method>
  <Variations>
    <Variation>Add 8 ozs of mushrooms, chopped and sautéed</Variation>
    <Variation>Add 1/2 cup of undyed shelled Pistachios.</Variation>
    <Variation>Add 1/2 cup of sliced almonds.</Variation>
    <Variation>Add minced garlic.</Variation>
  </Variations>
</Recipe>